Auto Acceptance Corporation v. Joseph Veneziano Submitted September 14 decided October 15, 1964 Submitted September 22

decided October 15, 1964

Submitted September 28

decided October 15, 1964

Arthur M. Lewis, in support of the petition. Theodore A. Lubinsky, in opposition. Theodore A. Lubinsky, in support of the motion. Arthur M. Lewis, in opposition. Theodore A. Lubinsky, in support of the motion.

The petition by the plaintiff for certification for appeal from the Appellate Division of the Circuit Court is denied.

The motion by the defendant to strike the notice of petition for certification for appeal from the Appellate Division of the Circuit Court, to terminate the stay of proceedings and enter judgment of the Appellate Division and to order the clerk not to accept the petition is denied.

The motion by the defendant to dismiss the petition for certification for appeal from the Appellate Division of the Circuit Court is denied.
